// Go workspace for the ledger.
//
// DEFAULT = the baseproof/tessera FORK. The committed workspace links the
// in-repo `third_party/tessera` submodule (module path
// github.com/transparency-dev/tessera — the fork is a drop-in) so every
// `go build` / `go test` / the release image uses the fork's deterministic
// Appender.Shutdown (drain + cancel + JOIN). See tessera/FORK.md.
//
//   - Build the fork (default): `git submodule update --init third_party/tessera`,
//     then any go command. CI + scripts/local/Dockerfile init the submodule.
//   - Opt out to Google upstream: `GOWORK=off go build ...` (ignores this
//     workspace → the go.mod-pinned transparency-dev/tessera) or
//     `make tessera-upstream` (drops ./third_party/tessera from the workspace).
//
// The witness daemon is hosted in its own repository
// (github.com/baseproof/tooling); it imports the same Baseproof SDK
// but resolves its module graph independently and never imports the ledger.

go 1.25.7

use (
	.
	./third_party/tessera
)
